modules.description: Provides functions to construct and send HTTP requests, parse JSON responses, and handle error cases during API interactions. Works with OCaml's `Lwt`-based asynchronous workflows, `Json.t` data structures, and HTTP client backends. Used to integrate with external services like authentication providers or data storage APIs in real-time applications.

Provides monadic operations for handling asynchronous I/O, including lifting values into the I/O context, mapping over results, and binding actions that return I/O values. Executes HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) with custom headers and returns responses as strings. Works with Lwt-based asynchronous values and error handling through a failure constructor.
